snippet.textDisplay: Pakistani coke studio is light years ahead of its Indian counterpart.. and this production is probably the best of the season.. starts as a soulful melody and suddenly gets catapulted to a different musical plane with the Eddie vedderish rock orgasmic yell by Umair jaiswal ... Umair and Balouch belong to contrasting genres but complement each other in an amazing fashion ... Strings as the producers match the brilliance of Rohail hyatt... Must listen!!!
snippet.textOriginal: Pakistani coke studio is light years ahead of its Indian counterpart.. and this production is probably the best of the season.. starts as a soulful melody and suddenly gets catapulted to a different musical plane with the Eddie vedderish rock orgasmic yell by Umair jaiswal ... Umair and Balouch belong to contrasting genres but complement each other in an amazing fashion ... Strings as the producers match the brilliance of Rohail hyatt... Must listen!!!

snippet.textDisplay: Addicted... brilliant bass line in the beginning ... soothing interplay with the mandolin... notes of raag pahadi on flute meander between the hillocks of balochistan to majestic mountains of himalayas instantly .. Umer jaiswal , the pioneer of new wave of Pakistani progressive rock starts in an impressive manner and to the amazement of listeners explodes in to a growl reminiscent of the hazy, glorious early days of the alternative rock taking the song to a whole new sonic dimension.... technical virtuosity of Quratulain balouch is a revelation and she nails it absolutely from the word go ...awesome piece on the acoustic guitar lends a brilliant transition .. the chemistry between the two vocalists belonging to different genres peaks and their immersion in the composition makes the song an audio as well as visual delight ...the drummer is probably one the most accomplished in Pakistan but he has to realise that in the history of rock there can be just one Keith moon .... multi layered orchestration conceals his shortcoming twice but he still does a phenomenal job... Strings, as producers take fusion music to dizzying heights!!
